<br>
Did I miss a patch message?  Can anyone else confirm this change?<br>
<br>
thanks,<br>
<br>
-Quelm, 53 Wanderer<br>
Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaharette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maharette</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/30/01 10:18:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scale of Wolf improved?</span><hr size=1> Scale was fixed a while back. It no longer drops if you are attacked, it drops when you attack back.  <p><img src="http://server2049.virtualave.net/jinwu/Mah-Cora2.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/30/01 12:20:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scale of Wolf improved?</span><hr size=1> Previously scale would stay up until one of the following happened:  you cast a spell or effect, you attacked something, something cast a spell on you, or the timer expired.  In my experience, melee attacks by mobs never caused it to drop.  Spells on the other hand, did cause it to drop.  When did the part about spells change?<br>
<br>
-Quelm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaelstormracer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gael Stormracer</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 2:40:51 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://content.communities.msn.com/isapi/fetch.dll?action=view_photo&ID_Community=GaelStormracer&ID_Topic=2&ID_Message=24 width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scale of Wolf improved?</span><hr size=1> A little while back, it seems. Absor commented about it some weeks ago, and I'd say it's now FINALLY the Travel spell that it was intended to be. Of course, an upgrade that combines Improved Superior Camo, Scale of Wolf, and See Invisible would be better still, but I guess that's now wandering into Bard Territory. <p><a href=http://communities.msn.com/GaelStormracer>Gael Stormracer</a>, 
Soldier of Tunare of the 50th Summer on Brell  <i><a href=http://www.eqcookeryandspirits.com>Cookery and Spirits</a></i><br>
<small>Master Brewer(180), Smith(176), Tailor(150), Baker (142), Fletcher (137), Potter (135) and Fisher (177).</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upantheaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pantheaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 3:18:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scale of Wolf improved?</span><hr size=1> Aye, everyone who's posted to this point is correct<br>
<br>
Scale will &quot;not&quot; drop if:<br>
1)You are casted upon and do not attack/cast to retaliate.<br>
2)You are struck in mellee combat and do not attack/cast to retaliate.<br>
<br>
<br>
Scale &quot;will&quot; drop if:<br>
1)You attack with casting/mellee retaliation<br>
2)You are attacked by mellee damage and have ANY type of damage shield whether it be Fire, Thorns, this also includes the Druid/Ranger self only AC/Dmg shield series of buff. The dmg shield WILL act as a natural retaliation thus you attacking the npc/pc and poof there goes Scale of Wolf.<br>
<br>
 <p>Panthea lvl 53 Druid of Brell <BR>
Member Sphere of Honor <BR>
Proud groupie of Naakor :P <BR>
Seamstress of 159 Thimbles</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadembird.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adem Bird</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ing.dk/images/abird.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 3:37:41 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ing.dk/images/ademfeet.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scale of Wolf improved?</span><hr size=1> Its actualy not so bad a spell anymore, I often use it in SoV, running peoble from Iceclad to Cobalt Scars its not a bad idea. <br>
<br>
Would love an item with Scale of Wolf as effect, cause I am often to lazy to mem it just to run throug SK or smething.<br>
<br>
Adem Bird <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showMessage?topicID=2398.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showMessage?topicID=2392.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.emailToFriend?topicID=2448.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.threadControl?topicID=2448.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2448.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2448.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm16">Velious<option value="thedruidsgrovekunark">Kunark<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovehuntingguide">Hunting Guide<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidicequipment">Druidic Equipment<option value="thedruidsgroveclassbalanceissues">Class Balance Issues<option value="thedruidsgrovethetrading